Yes it has certainly been a year!!! I’m not normally one to post the cliche montage videos but after the year I had, I wanted to celebrate! Because Lord knows the year before wasn’t so great.

In short, I am looking back on this year and with a tremendous amount of gratitude. Thank you to everyone who picked me up off the floor and helped me get out of the dark place I was in & made me whole again. You know who you are and I thank you. 

I have the greatest family , friends and jobs and I’m eternally grateful for the chapters in this thing called life. Cheers to 2023 🥂

At this point it’s no mystery how much I love @mercedesbenzusa . I was in a terrible accident a few months back when someone made an illegal turn right into me and my Mercedes saved me from what could’ve been a terrible / tragic accident. 
I will never drive another car other than a @mercedesbenz. Not even just saying that. 

So last week when they asked me to come test drive some of the new #AMG #EQS electric vehicles, I jumped at the opportunity. Saving lives and doing their part to help save the environment. Win Win. ⚡️.

There are not enough words to adequately articulate my gratitude for this past football season. It was unequivocally the greatest year of my professional career , which at this point has been hmmm 15 years??! But I’m only 29 🤔 😉so that doesn’t make sense … point is, I’m grateful beyond measure. 

✨ @nflonfox and the brass there allowed me the opportunity to not only work another year with their amazing team but also join another at @nflonprime . 

✨Being able to work FOR and ON two NFL platforms is a dream come true and I will NEVER take it for granted. I’m humbled to work with the greatest teammates at both Fox & Prime 🤍

✨I am not married , I don’t have kids and Fox / Prime are my family. This isn’t work to me, it’s my life and I don’t say that to be grand. My colleagues are my best friends , brothers , sisters and I’m forever grateful to live out my childhood dream with the best group of people on and off camera. No this isn’t an acceptance speech for an award I didn’t win, it’s a simple thank you to everyone who lets me do this & for everyone I get to do this with. I love you all & you know who you are 🙏🏽🤍

A bit about how House & Home started. 

Our Founder Charissa Thompson dreamt of starting an interior design company but never had the time, until Quarantine. (insert silver lining) She always wanted to help others love their space and in April 2020 she stopped thinking about it and started doing it. Almost three years later , we can say we've successfully turned MANY houses into homes!⁠
⁠
Want to redecorate your house but not sure where to start? House & Home is a full service interior design firm offering both virtual and in-person consultations from coast-to-coast. Send us a DM to learn more!

This Week = Nyc, Vegas, Ranch

So I did it… I recently bought a Ranch & fully renovated it as a vacation home. @rubyranchlife 

I know I know, I’m that chick. I watched Yellowstone, fell in love with a Ranch Renovation idea & did it. 

But this was not just any renovation … let me tell you, this was my biggest project to date and I couldn’t have done it without @roadwaymoving . 

I have used their services before and was SO impressed , I didn’t think to use anyone else for this move . And this wasn’t just any move. 

The Ranch is 75 acres in the middle of central California and not an easy location to get in and out for movers but my team rocked it! 

This two day move reminded me again why I will NEVER use any other company. 

So THANK YOU Roadway and if you need professional , friendly & incredible movers… use @roadwaymoving #movewithroadway #roadwaymoving they are truly the BEST!!!!!!!

My first experience going to a race track was with my grandpa when I was 8 years old. I fell in love with horse racing and even used to leave @extratv and go to Santa Anita and bet on the ponies before I had to go work red carpets 🤦🏼‍♀️. Didnt know the actors I was interviewing later that night but I knew the jockeys and the favorites in each race that afternoon! 

Soooooo , I say all this to express my excitement that I get to work the @belmontstakes for @foxsports tomorrow with the very best in the sport 🐎 and my second favorite jockey … Mike Smith! I already told Mike that Joel Rosario has my heart & being the class act he is , he said Joel deserves it! ❤️

As I write this I am in the car on my way from Philly to DC for an interview with NFL films and simultaneously working on details for what could be my biggest house & home project to date. @houseandhome.design ( so here’s a professional pic of me sitting on my bed ). @jonvolk @dominiquediazz @lyndsayzmakeup 

The “off-season” isn’t really an OFF season in my world… which is just fine by me! We get it.. I’m busy and a hero. But in all seriousness I need to do a better job of engaging with wonderful people on here that take the time to care abt anything I am doing in my life…. 

Soooo I say all this to setup a Q & A because I have 3 hours in the car so fire away… what questions do you have abt design , sports , anything! Don’t be weird… you know I have to say that cause there is always one dude that wants to talk about feet. 

#Q&A

My girl & her baby boy 💙 The sweetest story of Mack Roger Stoll as told by his momma @erinandrews on this weeks episode. 

💙Erin honestly explains the highs and lows of the 10 year journey she had to go on to become a Mom. And even though I’ve known this big secret of Mack for the last 9 months I get emotional listening to her talk knowing all she and @stolly28 did to make their dreams of becoming parents a reality. And their incredible surrogate who is a real life angel. 

💙 Also in true Erin fashion she is funny, self deprecating and sweet when describing the birth of her son. New episode out now @calmdownpodcast , grab your tissues for tears of joy and this episode is a reminder that there is good in this world!
